                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">339.115 General Motors Export Co./144:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-17T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 17, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Your despatch 2483 of May 10, 1935 and telegram No. 63 of May 16. You are
                    authorized to address a supplementary note to the Dominican Government along the
                    lines suggested in the last paragraph of the above despatch.</p>
                <pb facs="0593" n="500" xml:id="pg_500"/>
                <p>If you ascertain that American interests in the Dominican Tobacco Company are
                    sustaining injury as a result of the continued imprisonment of the President of
                    the Company you are authorized to add it as an additional point.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
